    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T23:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9367: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 14, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 14—10:45
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>477. At midnight on 13th Shanghai Office of Ministry of Foreign Affairs stated it
                    was instructed to notify all foreign diplomatic and consular representatives to
                    instruct their respective nationals to remove from the Hongkew and Yangtzepoo
                    areas to other places as quickly as possible. Warning is being given Americans
                    concerned.</p>
                <p>2. Chinese air craft are bombing at Shanghai. I am confidentially informed that
                    American aviators have threatened to join Chinese air forces. It is intimated
                    that Colonel Chennault,<note n="2" xml:id="d450fn2">Claire L. Chennault.</note>
                    retired officer United States Army Air Corps, now believed to be at Nanking, is
                    implicated.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Nanking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
